# Quality Rules — SOCA V1

## TypeScript
- Keep types strict.
- Avoid `any` unless justified with a short comment.

## Verification
- Before declaring "done", run `/verify` and report:
  - what commands were run
  - pass/fail
  - any follow-up TODOs

## Code health
- Keep functions small.
- Prefer clear naming over cleverness.
- Do not refactor unrelated areas inside a slice.
